        "content": "<p>Do we have some variant of this? If not, what are the necessary typeclass hypotheses to prove it?</p>",
        "id": 479304129,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1730129991
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"387244\">@Yaël Dillies</span></p>",
        "id": 479304160,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1730129998
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, we don't have it. The precise condition you need is that <code>(x + ·)</code> is an order embedding. It happens that we don't have a nice set of typeclasses that implies that</p>",
        "id": 479304521,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1730130083
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>CovariantClass α α (· + ·) (· ≤ ·)</code> + <code>ContravariantClass α α (· + ·) (· ≤ ·)</code> should do</p>",
        "id": 479304756,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1730130134
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ehm, do you know what those typeclasses are named now? A recent refactor renamed them</p>",
        "id": 479305074,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1730130218
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There's still <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=CovariantClass#doc\">docs#CovariantClass</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=ContravariantClass#doc\">docs#ContravariantClass</a>, but I think you can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddLeftMono#doc\">docs#AddLeftMono</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=AddLeftReflectLE#doc\">docs#AddLeftReflectLE</a></p>",
        "id": 479305464,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1730130314
    },
